  "Shoresh": [
   {
    "text": "Shoresh is a grammatical entity in Hebrew and Aramaic. ",
    "type": "text"
   },
   {
    "topLevelNodes": [
     {
      "ordinal": "-",
      "ordered": false,
      "tokensOfLine": [
       {
        "text": "An example of a shoresh is “א-כ-ל,” which represents the idea of “eating.”",
        "type": "text"
       }
      ],
      "children": []
     },
     {
      "ordinal": "-",
      "ordered": false,
      "tokensOfLine": [
       {
        "text": "A shoresh is used to produce many related words, like אוֹכֶל, which means “food,” or אֲכִילָה, which means “the act of eating.”",
        "type": "text"
       }
      ],
      "children": []
     },
     {
      "ordinal": "-",
      "ordered": false,
      "tokensOfLine": [
       {
        "text": "The shoresh is just a series of letters and is not itself a word, and has no vowels or pronunciation.",
        "type": "text"
       }
      ],
      "children": []
     },
     {
      "ordinal": "-",
      "ordered": false,
      "tokensOfLine": [
       {
        "text": "Advanced students can ",
        "type": "text"
       },
       {
        "text": "learn more about the concept of shoresh",
        "type": "local",
